  "title": "Project Executive",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Lead the end-to-end execution of projects.</li>\n  <li>Develop detailed project plans, including scope, timelines, resources, and budgets.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with internal teams and external stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Track project progress and address any delays or challenges proactively.</li>\n  <li>Manage project risks, safety compliance, and quality control measures.</li>\n  <li>Ensure project documentation is up to date and aligned with regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Report regularly to management on project status, cost performance, and key milestones.</li>\n  <li>Support post-project evaluations and continuous improvement initiatives.</li>\n  <li>Ad hoc assignments as tasked</li>\n</ol>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least a Diploma holder in any fields.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of experience in project management.</li>\n  <li>Strong leadership and coordination skills with the ability to manage multiple projects concurrently.</li>\n  <li>Excellent problem-solving, communication, and stakeholder management abilities.</li>\n  <li>Willingness to travel overseas when required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Position Overview</strong></u></p>\n<p>We are looking for a proactive and hands-on Project Executive to oversee the planning, execution, and completion of any assignments given. The ideal candidate will be responsible for managing cross-functional teams, liaising with clients and vendors, and ensuring projects are completed on time.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em>Please share your updated resume along with your reason(s) for leaving previous roles, expected salary, and notice period so we can process your application faster.</em></p>",
